net.gini.android.vision.accounting.network

Class GiniVisionAccountingNetworkService

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.gini.android.vision.accounting.network.GiniVisionAccountingNetworkService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GiniVisionNetworkService

    public class GiniVisionAccountingNetworkService
extends java.lang.Object
implements GiniVisionNetworkService
    Implementation using the Gini Accounting API of the network related tasks required by the Gini Vision Library.

    Relies on the Gini API SDK for executing the requests, which implements communication with the Gini Accounting API using generated anonymous Gini users.

    Important: Access to the Gini User Center API is required which is restricted to selected clients only. Contact Gini if you require access.

    To create an instance use the GiniVisionAccountingNetworkService.Builder returned by the GiniVisionAccountingNetworkService.builder(Context) method.

    In order for the Gini Vision Library to use this implementation pass an instance of it to GiniVision.Builder#setGiniVisionNetworkService(GiniVisionNetworkService) when creating a GiniVision instance.

      • getAnalyzedCameraPictureAsJpeg

        public byte[] getAnalyzedCameraPictureAsJpeg()
        Get the last successfully analyzed picture taken by the camera.

        Important: Call this method before calling GiniVisionAccountingNetworkService.cleanup() (or GiniVision#cleanup(Context)), otherwise it will return null.

        Returns:
        a byte array containing the picture in jpeg format. Returns null, if GiniVisionAccountingNetworkService.cleanup() (or GiniVision#cleanup(Context)) was called before or the analyzed document was not an image taken by the camera with the Gini Vision Library.
